# Logging Workflow

## Trigger

At the end of **any session** where a `.cursor/rules/` file was created or updated, generate a Notion log entry summary unprompted, formatted and ready to copy.

## Output Format

Present the following exactly — no extra commentary before or after:

---

**Entry Title:** [short label, e.g. "Episode Listings Overhaul — April 29"]
**Date:** [today's date]
**Files Changed:** [list the .mdc files touched this session]
**Session Summary:** [one to two sentences on what was accomplished]
**Process or Workflow Established:** [any repeatable pattern captured in the rules]
**Issues and Stumbles:** [what went wrong or required iteration]
**How It Was Fixed:** [the resolution and what it revealed]
**Synthesis Candidate:** [Yes or No — and a one-line reason]

---

## Rules

- Present this at the end of the session, not when asked
- Do not ask the user if they want it — just produce it
- Use today's actual date, not a placeholder
- Keep each field tight — one to three lines max
- If multiple .mdc files were touched, list all of them under Files Changed
- "Synthesis Candidate" means: does this session contain a pattern or decision worth promoting into a higher-level rule or permanent doc? Yes if it established something reusable. No if it was purely content updates.
